President Biden visited the Mack Lehigh Valley Operations in Macungie, Pennsylvania, where he emphasized the importance of supporting American-based companies and creating union jobs. He discussed the Buy American Act and announced plans to raise the domestic content requirement for federal purchases from 55% to 75%. He also highlighted the need to strengthen critical supply chains and invest in industries such as electric vehicles and clean energy. President Biden stressed that American workers are the key to building a strong economy and combating climate change, and he expressed his commitment to investing in them. He concluded by saying that the United States has the potential to be the most powerful economic nation in the world, and that democracies can compete with autocracies if they work together.